The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems on graphs, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of computer science related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on finding solutions that are secluded or have a small neighborhood suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of graph theory (cs.GT). The applications in secure routing and community detection suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of networked systems (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
